race.comment: TAINO ROCKET (6) has built steadily into this campaign and looks ready to peak now with a month between runs. The drop in trip off the short break should suit and the blinkers go on for the first time to sharpen him up. Pannell back aboard adds confidence. Leading player. KALOSYNI (4) resumes for trainer/jockey Jess Tzaferis and appears to have come on nicely during the break, readied with two sharp pieces of work. Draws well in the middle and can make an immediate impact. ISLA'S FURY (8) got too far back as favourite last start at Murray Bridge but flashed home to miss narrowly. Likely to get back again from the draw but can reel them in if they overdo it up front. FLUTTERING RUBY (1) was a determined winner in town on debut. Faces tougher opposition now but has upside and is drawn well for Holder. No reason she can't go on with the job.
